RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 31600. FOR REGISTERED PA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A PA-RESTRICTED RACE(S) OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 13 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 13 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ORGANIZED CHAOS sprinted clear early on, raced under a hold into the far turn, roused through the stretch and remained safe under steady handling. CHARM ALARM chased the early leader racing two deep, moved up four wide into the upper stretch and finished gamely to the wire. DARLING DONNA chased the early leader from the inside and kept on willingly to the wire. ARROGANTE coaxed along from the outside, raced three deep in the drive and moved up to improve position. PHANCY PHILLY dropped back early off the early going, raced near the inside into the upper stretch and had not enough in the drive. UNION FOLLY raced mid pack early on, was six wide near the three sixteenths pole and had no late rally while racing from the outside. SCHNUER WILL raced off the early pace setters, was three to four wide around the far turn and lacked a bid. BOUND BY TRUTH was coaxed along early and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Phancy Philly
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, inside upper stretch, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Bound by Truth
ENTRY.OWNER: Stites Christine S and Stites Tracy

ENTRY.NAME: Schnuer Will
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 3-4 wide turn, lacked bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 21500. FOR REGISTERED PA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HE IS BAD vied for the early lead along the inside and kicked clear late under strong handling. BANJO vied for the early lead between rivals early on, dug in late racing four deep and narrowly got up for the place position. IF WE GET LUCKY pressed the three deep from the outside of foes and was outkicked in the final stages. MILLBANK MAN dropped back to race near the back of the pack early on, raced from the outside in the stretch and moved up to improve position. GURT'S WARRIOR settled off the early pace, raced four wide into the upper stretch and raced evenly with no closing run. ABBY'S SPIRIT was off slowly, raced near the inside around the far turn through the stretch and never threatened. WARRIOR'S WAY OUT failed to sustain a bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Millbank Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, outside bid, moved up

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 83. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $16,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn Natio nal since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCESS RUNAWAY showed good early foot to set the early pace along the inside and held gamely to be clear late under steady handling. GIFT OF GAB was off slowly, rushed two deep to lay just off the early leader and kept on gamely to the wire. MY MASTERPIECE chased the early pace three deep, raced from the outside in the lane and finished willingly to the wire. TWELVEO'CLOCKROCK was void of early speed, raced four wide near the quarter pole, angled in through the stretch run and moved up to improve position. ZIPPY JO chased the early pace, raced along the inside and weakened in the drive. IN GOOD TROUBLE coaxed along early, checked sharply from the inside near the three eighths pole, raced three to two deep in the lane and lacked a bid. SASSY BABE dropped back early and failed to respond. JUSTICE OR APPEAL chased the pace from the inside and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: T REX settled off the early going, made a good bid to move from the inside near the quarter pole, angled to race from the outside in the stretch and finished strongly to surge clear under strong handling. READY REWARD rated along early, raced near the rail past the three eighths pole and finished well to rally for the place position while racing four deep. RECYCLE tracked the pace from the inside and faded. BOCA GUY raced off the early pace, was near the outside of rivals in the stretch and lacked a bid. SENSIBLE JIM void of early speed, raced five deep into the upper stretch, shifted in and never threatened. SYNONYM stalked the pace three wide and retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 10800. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 13. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIBACHI tracked the early leader under a hold early on, challenged nearing the three sixteenths pole and edged up late under all out pressure racing two deep.
